#!/usr/bin/env zsh
# @name: zf-help
# @description: Show help and usage information for the ZSH Functions Library
# @category: core
# @keywords: help, documentation, usage, guide, info
# @usage: zf-help
# @example: zf-help

zf-help() {
  cat << 'EOF'
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
                  ZSH Functions Library - Help
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

A modern system for organizing and discovering zsh functions with:
  • Categorized organization
  • Fuzzy search with fzf
  • Keyword and description-based discovery
  • Easy function management

CORE COMMANDS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  zf-browse [query]       Interactive fuzzy search (requires fzf)
  zfb [query]             Alias for zf-browse

  zf-list [category]      List all functions or by category
  zfl [category]          Alias for zf-list

  zf-search <keyword>     Search by keyword (grep-based, no fzf)
  zfs <keyword>           Alias for zf-search

  zf-add <name> <cat>     Create a new function from template
  zfa <name> <cat>        Alias for zf-add

  zf-help                 Show this help message
  zfh                     Alias for zf-help

USAGE EXAMPLES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  # Browse all functions interactively
  zf-browse

  # Search for git-related functions
  zf-browse git

  # List all functions
  zf-list

  # List functions in a specific category
  zf-list git

  # Search for functions containing "commit"
  zf-search commit

  # Create a new function
  zf-add my-helper git

FUNCTION FORMAT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Each function file should include metadata comments:

  # @name: function_name
  # @description: What the function does
  # @category: category_name
  # @keywords: keyword1, keyword2, keyword3
  # @usage: function_name [arguments]
  # @example: function_name arg1 arg2

This metadata enables powerful search and discovery features.

CATEGORIES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Default categories:
  • git       - Git and version control helpers
  • text      - Text processing and manipulation
  • file      - File operations and management
  • docker    - Docker and container tools
  • dev       - Development utilities
  • system    - System administration
  • network   - Network tools and utilities

You can create custom categories with: zf-add <name> <new_category>

INSTALLATION
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Add to your ~/.zshrc:

  source /path/to/zsh-functions/init.zsh

Optional: Enable verbose loading messages:

  export ZSH_FUNCTIONS_VERBOSE=1
  source /path/to/zsh-functions/init.zsh

REQUIREMENTS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  • zsh (obviously!)
  • fzf (optional, for zf-browse)
    Install: brew install fzf  (macOS)
         or: apt install fzf   (Linux)

MORE INFORMATION
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Library location: $ZSH_FUNCTIONS_DIR
Documentation: See README.md in the library directory

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
EOF
}

# Execute if run directly
if [[ "${(%):-%x}" == "${0}" ]]; then
  zf-help "$@"
fi
